5|$|Contact was {{released}} on VHS and the (then new) DVD format in December 1997. Among the special features, the DVD contains three separate audio commentaries by director Zemeckis and producer Starkey, another by visual effects supervisors Ken Ralston and Stephen Rosenbaum, along with one by star <b>Jodie</b> <b>Foster.</b> Contact {{was released}} on Blu-ray Disc on October 6, 2009.|$|E
5|$|Sound {{designers}} Randy Thom, Tom Johnson, Dennis S. Sands and William B. Kaplan {{were nominated}} for the Academy Award for Best Sound but lost to Titanic. <b>Jodie</b> <b>Foster</b> was nominated the Golden Globe Award for Best Actress in a Motion Picture Drama, but Judi Dench was awarded the category for her work in Mrs Brown. Contact won the Hugo Award for Best Dramatic Presentation over The Fifth Element, Gattaca, Men in Black and Starship Troopers. The Academy of Science Fiction, Fantasy & Horror Films awarded individual awards to <b>Jodie</b> <b>Foster</b> (Best Actress) and Jena Malone (Best Performance by a Younger Actor) at the 24th Saturn Awards. Director Robert Zemeckis, writers James V. Hart and Michael Goldenberg, film score composer Alan Silvestri and the visual effects supervisors also received Saturn Award nominations. Contact was {{nominated for the}} Saturn Award for Best Science Fiction Film, but lost to Men in Black.|$|E
