5|$|On March 30, 1981, Ronald Reagan, 40th President of the United States, {{and three}} others were shot and wounded by John Hinckley Jr. in Washington, D.C., as they were leaving a {{speaking}} engagement at the Washington Hilton Hotel. Hinckley's motivation for the attack was to impress actress <b>Jodie</b> <b>Foster,</b> over whom he had developed an obsession after seeing her in the 1976 film Taxi Driver.|$|E
