50|$|While {{working as}} an {{assistant}} for production on <b>Jodie</b> <b>Foster's</b> film Home for the Holidays (1995), Snyder became ill with Chronic Fatigue Syndrome (CFS), a debilitating and complex disorder characterized by intense fatigue. I Remember Me (2000) became Snyder's biographical documentary debut She directed, produced, wrote and appeared in the film. It explored the history of and controversy behind CFS.|$|R
